cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper discusses the application of information theoretic losses to data selection methods in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the use of mathematical tools and analysis, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
